# Copy to `.env` in the repo root (never commit `.env`).
# Express loads this automatically via `import 'dotenv/config'` in `index.js`.

# ── Firebase Admin (local dev = staging project `roster-riddles-staging`) ─────────────
# Use ONE of these so `GET /api/v1/me` verifies the same tokens as the Angular app.
#
# Option A (recommended): path to the JSON key file from Firebase Console:
#   Firebase → Project settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key
#   Save as e.g. `secrets/roster-riddles-staging-adminsdk.json` (folder is gitignored).
#
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./secrets/roster-riddles-staging-adminsdk.json
#
# Option B: inline JSON (single line) — useful for some hosts; avoid in shared shells.
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account","project_id":"roster-riddles-staging",...}

# Optional: override port (default 3000). Angular `proxy.conf.json` proxies /api here.
# PORT=3000

# ── One-time: mirror Firestore `cache` from prod → staging (see docs/firestore-mirror.md) ─
# MIRROR_SOURCE_CREDENTIALS=./secrets/prod-service-account.json
# MIRROR_TARGET_CREDENTIALS=./secrets/roster-riddles-staging-adminsdk.json
# SOURCE_FIRESTORE_DATABASE_ID=roster-riddles
# TARGET_FIRESTORE_DATABASE_ID=
